HEADWORD: Madwort
<hw>Mad"wort`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
genus of cruciferous plants (<gen>Alyssum</gen>) with white or yellow
flowers and rounded pods. <spn>Alyssum maritimum</spn> is the commonly
cultivated sweet alyssum, a fragrant white-flowered annual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maeandra</ent>⟦br⟧
